{"timestamp": "2025-12-07 01:55:12.832329", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nScope and topology\\n- Environment: 3‑tier Clos (fat‑tree) using EBGP with FRR.\\n- Devices in scope: super_spine_router_0 (AS 65000), spine_router_0_0/0_1, leaf_router_0_0/0_1, hosts pc_0_0 (10.0.0.2/24 via 10.0.0.1), pc_0_1 (10.0.1.2/24 via 10.0.1.1).\\n- Host-facing subnets: 10.0.0.0/24 on leaf_router_0_0 (eth8), 10.0.1.0/24 on leaf_router_0_1.\\n\\nHigh-level assessment\\n- Control-plane health: EBGP sessions across super-spine ↔ spines and spines ↔ leaves are established; all expected /24s are present in routing tables.\\n- Data-plane health: End-to-end ICMP across the fabric is generally healthy with low RTT and 0% loss for many hosts.\\n- Anomaly: Only pc_0_0 exhibits complete IP connectivity failure, including to its default gateway. pc_0_1 is normal.\\n\\nDetected anomalies and localization\\n- Anomaly: pc_0_0 cannot ping any remote hosts or even its default gateway (10.0.0.1). Example: pc_0_0 -> pc_1_2/pc_3_3 status unknown/timeouts. Targeted pings from pc_0_0 to 10.0.0.1 also time out.\\n- Localization: Issue is isolated to host pc_0_0 (its local TCP/IP stack), not the fabric or its leaf.\\n  - pc_0_1 can ping its gateway (10.0.1.1) and remote hosts successfully.\\n  - leaf_router_0_0 fails to ping pc_0_0 (10.0.0.2), even though ARP resolves, indicating the host is not returning IP replies.\\n\\nEvidence and detailed findings\\n- pc_0_0 IP config is correct:\\n  - 10.0.0.2/24 on eth0, default via 10.0.0.1.\\n- L2 between pc_0_0 and leaf_router_0_0 is working:\\n  - pc_0_0 arping 10.0.0.1 succeeds (replies from 8e:86:ef:24:8f:56).\\n  - leaf_router_0_0 ARP table shows 10.0.0.2 lladdr 2e:32:25:ec:e6:37 and ARP probes succeed (arping 10.0.0.2 gets replies).\\n- IP/ICMP is blocked on pc_0_0:\\n  - All IP pings from pc_0_0 (to gateway or elsewhere) time out.\\n  - leaf_router_0_0’s ping to 10.0.0.2 (ICMP Echo) also receives no reply, consistent with local output filtering on pc_0_0.\\n- Root cause indicator on pc_0_0:\\n  - iptables -S shows a DROP in OUTPUT chain:\\n    - -A OUTPUT -m length --length 10:65535 -j DROP\\n  - This rule drops virtually all locally generated IP packets (and responses such as ICMP echo-replies), explaining total IP outage while L2/ARP still works.\\n- Routing control-plane state (selected):\\n  - leaf_router_0_0 has 10.0.0.1/24 on eth8 and BGP-learned routes to all other /24s via spines.\\n  - BGP summaries on leaves, spines, and super-spine show all neighbor sessions Established with appropriate prefixes exchanged.\\n  - No indications of routing blackholes or missing routes relevant to pc_0_0/pc_0_1 subnets.\\n\\nConclusions\\n- Anomaly present: Yes — complete IP connectivity failure isolated to host pc_0_0.\\n- Faulty device: pc_0_0 (end host).\\n- Root cause: Host firewall misconfiguration on pc_0_0 (iptables OUTPUT rule dropping packets of length 10–65535), which blocks all outbound IP traffic (including ICMP and responses to inbound probes). The underlay fabric and EBGP control-plane are healthy., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='4aabd6ce-a1d8-4944-82b5-91fdfd920639'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
